 By Festus Ahon – Asaba Delta State Governor, Senator Ifeanyi Okowa, weekend, said some prospective investors has indicated interest in the Kwale Industrial Park, expressing their readiness to commit funds to the project and relocate to Nigeria. Okowa speaking at The Natural Gas and Chemicals International Forum In Nanjing, China, expressed confidence that his trip to China was fruitful. The event with the theme “Nigeria: The Kwale Industrial Park Investment Opportunity”, had investors, consultants, federal government delegation as well as a delegation from the state in attendance. Continue reading Foreign investors indicate interests in Kwale Industrial Park ― Okowa at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Delta Governor, Sen. (Dr) Ifeanyi Okowa, on Friday said some prospective investors in Kwale Industrial Park in the state, had indicated readiness to commit funds to the project and relocate to Nigeria. Continue reading Okowa confirms interest of investors in Kwale Industrial Park at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard October 25, 2019 In "News" LEADERSHIP : In line with his administration’s commitment to the speedy industrialization of Delta State, Governor Ifeanyi Okowa has assured prospective investors in Kwale Industrial Park of quick return on investment. Governor Okowa stated this Asaba when the management of Temple Energy and GasInvest, joint consultants to the project briefed… July 25, 2019 In "News" Tribune Online ‘I will ensure Speedy take off of Kwale Industrial Park’ Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State has assured prospective investors in Kwale Industrial  Park of quick return on investments. Okowa spoke in Asaba when the management of Temple Energy and GasInvest, consultants to the industrial park project, briefed… July 31, 2019 In "News"